<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM Arrives in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul-Salam
Majali arrived here today leading a high-caliber delegation for an
official visit which will see a number of agreements signed.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian delegation, which includes 10 ministers, will
take part in the 14th meeting of the Egyptian-Jordanian Higher
Committee scheduled to start this evening.
</P>
<P>
The committee will discuss several joint projects between the
two sides in all domains, particularly in trade, industry and
economy.
</P>
<P>
Six agreements and protocols of bilateral cooperation in
economic and cultural fields will be signed during the two-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Talks will also cover several political issues of common
interest, atop of which the latest developments of the Mideast
peace process and efforts to defrost the Arab-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The Mideast peace march has slowed down since the deal on
Israeli partial withdrawal from Hebron was successfully brokered
by the U.S., Jordan and Egypt in January. An Israeli decision to
build a new neighborhood for Jews has stranded the peace talks for
three months.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Jordan, the only two Arab countries having peace
treaties with Israel, have played important mediator's roles in
the past Mideast peace negotiations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
