<HEADLINE> Ceasefire Agreement Violated in Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The ceasefire agreement between
rival factions of the Republic of Congo has been violated in its
capital Brazzaville, said reports monitored here today.
</P>
<P>
Another breakout of shelling and gunfire was heard in the city
as efforts to end the month-long civil war are continuing.
</P>
<P>
Residents in the city said it was not clear whether the latest
exchanges of fire were started by President Pascal Lissouba's
troops or the forces loyal to former president Sassou Sguesso.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the United Nations Security Council has expressed
support in principle to send an African peace keeping force to
Brazzaville.
</P>
<P>
UN special envoy to the central African region Mohammed
Sahnoun told reports that an international force would assist
diplomatic efforts to end the fighting there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
