<HEADLINE> Greek Magazine Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- the Europe-China Business Review
magazine hailed Hong Kong's return to China in an editorial to be
published next week.
</P>
<P>
The editorial spoke highly of the "one country, two systems"
principle which the Chinese government adopted to solve the Hong
Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
The principle, initiated by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping, is "a brave" experiment, the editorial said, adding that
its outcome is important not only for China and Asia, but also the
entire world.
</P>
<P>
The magazine said it hopes that Hong Kong will maintain its
prosperity after its return to China.
</P>
<P>
It said that with the principle of "one country, two systems,"
China will eventually realize its national reunification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
