<HEADLINE> Kenya confident in Hong Kong's New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Foreign Minister Kalonzo
Musyoka today said that the Kenyan government is confident in the
new administration of Hong Kong which began operation on July 1,
1997.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival from Hong Kong after attending the
handing-over ceremony, Musyoka said that Hong Kong would be
administered with high level autonomy which would ensure it
remains the world's finance center.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference held at the Jomo Kenyatta
International Airport, he said that Kenya had effectively warded
off an attempt to move the headquarters of the U.N. Environment
Program (UNEP) in Nairobi to other place.
</P>
<P>
Musyoka said that Germany, South Africa, Brazil and Singapore
had sought to introduce a declaration announcing the world
environmental body to be based in Germany. The Kenyan minister
had attended the 19th special session of the United Nations in
New York on the follow-up of the Earth Summit in Rio de Janeiro
five years ago.
</P>
<P>
There were also attempts to shift the HABITAT office from
Nairobi, but "we effectively countered them", he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
