<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's University Turns Out 2,400 Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa University
today graduated 2,423 under and post graduate students in
diplomas and degrees.
</P>
<P>
Among the graduates who have attended regular and continuing
education programs, 2,191 are under graduates while 232 are post
graduate students.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the graduation ceremony, President of the
university Mogessie Ashenafi said the number of this year's batch
exceeds that of the previous years.
</P>
<P>
Mogessie said the university has begun carrying out activities
with a view to producing capable citizens in every aspect of
development initiatives that the country is engaged in.
</P>
<P>
A teachers' evaluating system has been designed by the
administrative body of the university in a bid to encourage
assidous lectures, he added. 
