<HEADLINE> Dire Dawa Coca Cola Wins Regional Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Dire Dawa Coca Cola Factory
under the East Africa Bottling Company won the 1996 gold prize for
good quality, emerging victorious among 31 African countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, factory
Manager Tarekegn Kidane told local journalists today that 89
factories took part in the contest whose result was declared after
a 12 month sample study by the coca cola international supervisors.
</P>
<P>
Tarekegn said that the factory functioning with old machineries and
backward technology managed to win its competitors with modern
technology thanks to the relentless efforts of its workers.
</P>
<P>
The prize prepared by the president of Coca Cola-Northern Africa
was handed over to the factory's manager by Jerry Day, technical
services director at the company's northern Africa office.
</P>
