<HEADLINE> European MP Arrives in Amman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Member of European Parliament (EP)
Magda Aveloet arrived here this evening on a five-day working visit
to write a report on various aspects of Jordan.
</P>
<P>
An "honest" report will be written about the country's
general situation, particularly the political and economic
aspects, said Aveloet, who is a rapporteur of the EP Committee on
Foreign Affairs, Security and Defense Policy.
</P>
<P>
Her report will help the EP evaluate an association agreement
between the kingdom and the European Union (EU), according to
Aveloet.
</P>
<P>
During her visit, Aveloet will meet some Jordanian cabinet
ministers. She will also meet the chairpersons of the Foreign
Affairs Committee of the Upper and Lower Houses as well as other
officials.
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, Jordan has been trying to secure a
partnership with the EU and join the World Trade
Organization. 
</P>
