<HEADLINE> Youth Drug Abuse Alarming in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Nigeria's National Drug
Law Enforcement Agency Musa Bamaiyi today expressed great concern
over drug abuse by youths in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that more than 90 percent of the mental cases treated
in psychiatrical hospitals in Nigeria can be attributable to drug
abuse by youths.
</P>
<P>
This development, he said, is posing great threat to the
future of the country's economy and image abroad, as well as the
standard of medical care in the country.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony for launching a youth program organized by the
Nation Orientation Agency, Bamaiyi reminded parents of proper
education of their children.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the president of the National Orientation Agency
described the involvement of drug abuse by youths, examination
malpractices and armed robbery in the country as alarming.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has over recent years made great efforts to crack down
upon drug abuse and smuggling and some progress has been
reported. But what has been learned from today's ceremony paints
a grey picture of the result of the efforts.  
</P>
