<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Ends Dalian's Winning Streak in China Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou Apollo snapped Dalian
Wanda's winning streak in the seventh round but the defending
champion remained runaway leader in the standings of the 12-team
Chinese professional soccer league.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, which had won the first six rounds by outscoring its
rivals 11-1, salvaged a 1-1 draw as Zhang Enhua scored in a goal
melee at the 40th minute. Guangzhou opened the scoring at the
30th minute.
</P>
<P>
Two-time champion Dalian now tops the standings with 19 points,
seven points clear of 1995 champion Shanghai Shenhua, which at
home drew Tianjin Samsung 0-0.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Quanxing moved one place up to the third with 12 points
as it cashed in on home-turf advantage to beat August First
(Chinese Army) 4-0.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an downed Qingdao Hainiu 2-0 to place fourth with
10 points.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, Yanbian Aodong edged Vanguard Huandao
2-1 and Jinan Taishan beat Guangdong Hongyuan 2-0.
</P>
<P>
At the bottom of the table, Yanbian, Tianjin and Guangdong
finished 10th, 11th and last. 
</P>
