<HEADLINE> Building Sale-Purchase Deals Up in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The amount of the building
sale-and-purchase deals grew in Hong Kong in the first six months
of this year, the Land Registry Department said today.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period, a total of 115,673 sale and
purchase agreements of building units, which included both
residential and non-residential properties, were received for
registration by the department.
</P>
<P>
It quoted its land registration statistics as saying that the
figure represented an increase of 71.5 percent and 44.6 percent
compared with the first and second halves of 1996 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of the considerations involved in these
agreements was 483.58 billion Hong Kong dollars (about 62.48
billion U.S. dollars), which was up by 145.3 percent and 74.2
percent compared with the two preceding half-yearly periods.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 110,980 assignments of building units were lodged for
 registration in the first six months of the year, compared with
78,255 and 81,265 respectively recorded during the first and
second halves of last year, showing an increase of 36.6 percent
and 41.8 percent respectively, the department added.
</P>
<P>
It said that the total amount of the considerations involved,
amounting to 378.04 billion Hong Kong dollars (about 48.84 billion
 U.S. dollars), showed an increase of 103.9 percent and 66.5
percent respectively when compared with the two preceding
half-yearly periods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
