<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doohan Wins Seventh Motorcycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Michael Doohan, on an
Honda, won the Imola grand prix for his seventh win in eight
starts in the 500cc world motorcycling championship in Imola on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian suffered a terrible start from pole position and
had to ride through the field to restore his supremacy.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Nobuatsu Aoki led from the first turn and the Suzuki of
Australian Anthony Gobert tucked in behind him, leaving Doohan in
fourth spot.
</P>
<P>
However by the seventh of the 25 laps, Doohan had regained the
lead and eventually cruised to his 41st grand prix victory by 8.6
seconds from Nobuatsu Aoki. Doohan even clocked the fastest lap
in his penultimate circuit at the Dino Farrari venue.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Checa of Spain, second to Doohan in official qualifying,
nearly had a nasty accident four laps from home as he slid off
into the gravel. But he cleverly negotiated the dangerous surface
before rejoining the race.
</P>
<P>
Max Biaggi of Italy won the 250cc event, increasing his
overall lead in the world championship standings, ahead of fellow
Honda riders Olivier Jacque of France and Japan's Tohru Ukawa.
</P>
<P>
In the 125cc competition, Italian Valentino Rossi on an Aprilia
took the event. He finished ahead of Japan's Honda riders Tomomi
Manako and Kazuto Sakata. 
</P>
</TEXT>
