<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Building Its Biggest Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Construction started here today on
the Tibet Autonomous Region's largest park.
</P>
<P>
Located in the western part of this capital city of the region,
the Riyuehu park (sun-moon lake park) will occupy an area of 26.4
ha and cost a total of 70 million yuan to complete. The fund will
be provided by a businessman from Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The park will be a complex of hotels, lakes, gardens, cultural
facilities and a special center for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Statues of King Gesar, Songtsan Gambo and Princess Wen Cheng,
important figures in the history of Tibet, will be erected in the
park, to highlight the tibetan culture.
</P>
<P>
 
