<HEADLINE> Malaysia Airlines Suspends Flights to Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Airlines (MAS) has
canceled all flights to Phnom Penh, the capital city of Cambodia,
indefinitely due to the deteriorating political situation in that
country, Malaysian Transport Minister Ling Liong Sik said today.
</P>
<P>
"It seems that the political situation in that country is
becoming more serious and in the interest of the safety of
passengers, MAS has decided that all flights to Phnom Penh be
stopped until peace is restored in that country," Ling said.
</P>
<P>
MAS would review the developments in Phnom Penh from time to
time before deciding when to resume its flights there, the
minister told reporters after opening a conference of the
Malaysian Chinese Association (MCA) in Genting Highlands, 35 kms
northeast of Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
MAS canceled today's flight from Kuala Lumpur to Phnom Penh
scheduled for this morning and its flight back from Phnom Penh to
Kuala Lumpur scheduled for this evening.
</P>
<P>
The current situation in Cambodia, which is scheduled to
officially join the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
later this month, defeated the spirit of ASEAN to make its member
countries more prosperous by bringing in investors, traders and
tourists, Ling commented.  
</P>
</TEXT>
