<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai-HK Cooperation To Enter New Era </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to the
motherland will usher in a new period of economic cooperation
between Shanghai and Hong Kong, according to Shanghai Mayor Xu
Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
Xu made the statement in an article in the latest issue of
"Shanghai Today" magazine. He said that the economic ties between
the two metropolises have shown a new trend ever since China
adopted the reform and opening policy in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said that the scale of the cooperation has been
enlarged day by day, as the two-way trade increased from 1.7
billion US dollars-worth in 1989 to 3.64 billion US dollars-worth
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hong Kong investors have expanded the scope of their
investment from industrial fields to the financial, commercial and
real estate sectors. In addition, they have turned from direct
investment to indirect financing, including helping local
enterprises with bank loans, the issue of b-shares, h-shares and
setting up cooperative funds.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Shanghai has also begun to invest in Hong
Kong, which has resulted in a two-way flow of funds, the mayor
noted.
</P>
<P>
He continued that Shanghai and Hong Kong should further enhance
their economic cooperation, based on the principles of being
mutually complementary and mutual beneficial, developing unitedly,
and achieving common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The mayor suggested that the two areas should further cooperate
in the fields of service, banking and trade, as well as in hi-tech
industries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two places should also step up their cooperation
in the fields of communications, telecommunications and urban
infrastructure, the mayor stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
