<HEADLINE> 6 People Killed in Torrential Rains in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed as
torrential rains hit northwestern and western provinces of Iran,
destroying roads, washing away homes and inundating farms, Tehran
Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The state-run radio said that provinces that suffered most are
West Azarbaijan, East Azarbaijan and Ardebil in northwestern Iran
and Kurdestan province in the west of the country.
</P>
<P>
The floods caused by continuous rainfall in the past 24 hours
have also killed some 1,500 heads of cattle, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, seven people died and 18 injured
after Friday night's rainfall, due to severe floods in Eastern
Azarbaijan.
</P>
<P>
The floods also led to the derailing of a passenger train en
route from the provincial capital of Tabriz to Tehran. Three
railway carriages were derailed and about 18 passengers were
injured due to the mishap. 
</P>
</TEXT>
