<HEADLINE> Australian Wins Third Triathlon World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Australian Emma Carney on Sunday
clinched her third victory in the season's fourth leg of the World
Cup triathlon series in Gamagori, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Carney, 1994 world champion, was never the fastest in the three
sections, but her steady performance made her world number one.
</P>
<P>
She was 20th in the 1.5km swimming, seventh in the 40km bike
race and second in the 10km run for a combined time of 2:03:44.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Kiyomi Niwata finished second in 2:04.07 and American
Barb Lindquiest was third at 2:04:09.
</P>
<P>
In the men's competition, Brad Beven of Australia came first in
1:48:00, beating Hamish Carter of New Zealand by 27 seconds and
Stephan Bignet of France by 49 seconds. 
