<HEADLINE> India's Petrochemical Products Demand to Double By </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The demand for petrochemical
products in India will almost double by the year 2001, according
to a study published by the Federation of Indian Chambers of
Commerce and Industry (FICCI) today.
</P>
<P>
A boom in agriculture, food processing, power and
telecommunication sectors will mainly contribute to the increased
demand, which is expected to touch nine million tons as against
5.1 million tons in 1995, the study says.
</P>
<P>
The FICCI has suggested focusing on skilled manpower
availability and attracting foreign direct investment to sustain
the demand.
</P>
<P>
But the FICCI also said that it is difficult to find the right
kind of feed-stock for various uses in the industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
