<HEADLINE> Iranian Protesters Call for War with Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 5,000 demonstrators burned
Israeli and U.S. flags in front of the United Nations office
building here today to protest against the Israeli posters
depicting Islam's Prophet Mohammed as a pig.
</P>
<P>
Chanting "Death to America" and "Death to Israel", the angry
protesters called for war with Israel while appealing to the
Islamic community to get united to confront what they called the
Israeli plots and condemning the U.S. support for the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
"To destroy the Zionist army, we must go through a sea of
blood," the crowd chanted.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators, mostly clothed in black, held placards that
read "Israel Rushing toward Doomsday" and "the Army of God is
Ready."
</P>
<P>
Seyyed Ahmad Khatami, a clergyman who teaches at Iran's
influential Qom Islamic seminary, told the crowd that the Israelis
who were involved in making the posters must be executed.
</P>
<P>
"The person who drew the picture, the owner of the printing
house that printed it, all are condemned to death," Khatami said.
</P>
<P>
"The only way to end these insults is through destruction of
Israel," the clergyman said and called on the Muslim activists
around the world to attack Israeli interests.
</P>
<P>
Last week, posters showing the Muslim Prophet Mohammed as a pig
writing the holy Koran were pasted on more than 20 Palestinian
stores near the downtown of the West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
The incident has aroused great anger among Arab states and
ignited a fresh round of violence in the West Bank and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Israeli authorities last week detained Tatiana Susskind, 25,
a resident of Jerusalem, for the drawing of the pictures.
</P>
