<HEADLINE> Nigerian Male Life Expectancy Puts at 49 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The life expectancy of Nigerian men
and women was estimated at 49 and 56 years respectively between
(UNFPA).
</P>
<P>
A survey by UNFPA shows only 66 percent of Nigerians had
access to health services between 1985 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
It puts the country's population at 115 million in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The percentage of the population with access to health
services#,UNFPA explained, is "the percentage of the population
that can reach appropriate local health services by the local
means of transport in no more than one hour."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the percentage of Nigerians with access to safe
water between 1990 and 1994 was estimated at 39 percent, while 36
percent had access to sanitation in the same period. 
</P>
