<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) has provided about 1.6 million
U.S. Dollars to Tanzania for repairing the road between Nyakanazi
and Kibondo in western Tanzania, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement to this effect which was signed here
on Friday, a portion of the money would be used for repair work
at Simbo area on the Kigoma-Kasulu Road about 15 kilometers from
the regional headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The upgrading of the road will facilitate the planned
repatriation of refugees from the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR Representative to Tanzania Lennart Kotsalainen said at
the signing ceremony that if the road is not repaired, it would
hinder the transport of refugees to camps and the whole
repatriation exercise.
</P>
<P>
The repair work is scheduled to start next week and will be
completed in January.
</P>
<P>
"The road between Nyakanazi and Kibondo area is an obstacle to
trucks transporting refugees from the border to camps," he noted.
</P>
