<HEADLINE> Israel Blamed for Worsening Situation in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The recent deteriorating security
situation in Hebron has been a result of the provocative policies
of the Israeli government, Palestinian ambassador to Zimbabwe Ali
Halimeh claimed.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the Sunday Mail paper, Halimeh said the new
Israeli administration is responsible for the collapse of the
negotiations between the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO)
and the Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''It is known to the entire world that Prime Minister
B. Netanyahu is not interested in a political settlement with the
Palestinians and he himself is to blame for the deteriorating
situation in the area.''
</P>
<P>
''The tension which is prevailing in the Middle East is a
result of the persistent policies of Netanyahu, policies which
reject basic principles of the peace Madrid conference and the
Oslo declaration of principles and the signed agreement between
the previous government and the PLO,'' Halimeh said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said the Netanyahu government has embarked on a
campaign to destabilize the Palestinian self-rule territories
through economic blockades and through their security
establishment and encouraging violence since it was formed.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Palestinian people will continue to
protect the achievement which has been made until the
establishment of the Palestinian independent state with Jerusalem
as its capital. 
