<HEADLINE> One Million Internet Users in S. Africa Predicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- South Africa could have one
million Internet users by the end of this year, local daily
Sunday Independent quoted a Web publisher as reporting today.
</P>
<P>
"There are already about 500,000 users in South Africa and at
the current private and corporate connectivity levels, it is not
unrealistic to expect it to reach the million mark by the end of
the year," Robin Parker, the marketing director of Africa, said.
</P>
<P>
By the turn of the century, the South African internet site
development and advertizing market could be worth one billion
Rand (222 million U.S. dollars), with more than two million Rand
of on line transactions a year, Parker said.
</P>
<P>
"Individual connectivity is growing by about 12 percent a
month and the usage of specific value sites is growing at between
20 percent and and 40 percent," he noted. 
</P>
