<DOCNO> XIE19970706.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> In Memory of the Marco Polo Bridge Incident  (Part One) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The year of 1997 sees the 60th
anniversary of the Marco Polo Bridge Incident, which militarist
Japan provoked to wage its all-out war of aggression against China.
</P>
<P>
As an old Chinese saying goes: "Past experience, if not
forgotten, is a guide for the future." Therefore, today, it is
absolutely necessary to look back upon Japanese militarists' war
of aggression against China and to draw a profound lesson from it.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary because there has always existed a small
right-wing force in Japan which denies Japan's history of
aggression.
</P>
<P>
Those people became even more active in recent years,
intensifying their efforts to eulogize and whitewash Japanese
militarism and tried hard to reverse the verdict on Japan's
invasion of other Asian nations, including China.
</P>
<P>
They said Japan was defending its "legitimate rights" when it
forced the 21 Demands on China in 1915, which was aimed at
dominating China, and when it launched the September 18 Incident
in 1931, which was a significant step toward Japan's occupation of
the entire northeast of China.
</P>
<P>
They claimed the Marco Polo Bridge Incident was not created by
the Japanese side and instead was the work of the Chinese troops.
</P>
<P>
They even alleged the Rape of Nanjing (Nanking) in 1937 was
"merely fabrication."
</P>
<P>
By these remarks of utmost absurdity, they distorted history to
the utmost degree, thus severely hurting the feelings of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Their moves cannot but make people highly vigilant. What on
earth do they intend to?
</P>
<P>
Opening the historical records which are not yet dust-laden, we
can easily find that Japan's invasion and occupation of China was
a long-premediated ambition of the Japanese militarists.
</P>
<P>
The notorious (Giichi) Tanaka Memorial to the Throne in 1927
revealed Japan's ambition of annexing China as part of its
strategy to conquer and dominate the world as early as in the
1920s.
</P>
<P>
It was under the strategy of the Tanaka memorial -- "to conquer
China, we must first conquer Manchuria and Mongolia; to conquer
the whole world, we must first conquer China" -- that the Japanese
militarists provoked the September 18 Incident and concocted the
so-called Manchuria state within China.
</P>
<P>
It was under the same strategy that, Japan, after deliberate
planning, created the Marco Polo Bridge Incident on July 7, 1937
and later spread the flames of war to more than two thirds of
Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
During the war, Japanese aggressor troops desperately
implemented the policy of "kill all, loot all and burn all" on
Chinese soil, and even used biological and chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
The atrocities that Japan inflicted upon China were the most
barbarous and most brutal in human history.
</P>
<P>
Japan's aggression against China was unprecedented in human
history in terms of duration, scale and damage. More
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970706.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
