<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading Japanese newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Mortars and rockets slammed down on several parts of the
Cambodian capital Saturday after the rival forces of the country's
fending co-premiers battled near the city's airport.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- An early summer heat wave continued to broil Tokyo and
surrounding areas Saturday, with the mercury soaring to 40.2
centigrade degree in Koshigaya, Saitama Prefecture, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Yomiuri:
</P>
<P>
-- A growing number of Japanese believe that the country is not
as safe as it used to be, according to the results of a Yomiuri
Shimbun survey.
</P>
<P>
Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- The Pathfinder spacecraft tumbled to a halt Friday on a
boulder-strewn plain, ending two decades of inactivity in Mars
exploration and launching a new campaign to search for clues of
past life on the Red Planet. 
