<HEADLINE> In Memory of the Marco Polo Bridge Incident  (Part Two) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to official statistics, as many as 35 million Chinese
were killed or wounded during the war of aggression.
</P>
<P>
Calculated by the exchange rates of 1937, the direct damage
which Japan caused to China reached as high as 100 billion
U.S. dollars, while the indirect damage 500 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The monstrous crime that Japanese militarists committed in
China, human testimony and material evidence which is still there
will by no means disappear with the mere disavowals of a handful
of Japanese.
</P>
<P>
The more they try to cover it up, the more the crime will be
exposed. What the small group of Japanese are doing will only
make the already shameful historical records of Japan all the more
disgusting.
</P>
<P>
