<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Freight Outpaces Passenger Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Air freight grew fastest of all
cargo transportation in the first four months of the year,
outpacing passenger transportation, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
China shipped 380,200 tons of freight by air, an 8.4 percent
increase from the same period of 1996. Passenger transportation
grew 5.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Total freight volume was 868 million tons in the four-month
period, a 1 percent fall from the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Rail freight fell 1 percent to 529 million tons; truck freight
fell 1.1 percent to 141 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Freight by boat fell 0.9 percent to 197 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Passengers totaled 1.7 billion, a 1.7 percent increase from the
first four months of 1996. Railway travel rose 0.8 percent to 307
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
