<HEADLINE> Microcomputer Production Rises in First Five Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China is becoming a major computer
product trader, today's China Daily quoted Yang Dongqing of the
information center of the Ministry of Electronics Industry (MEI)
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Customs statistics show China sold 290,000 microcomputers
abroad during the first five months, up 15 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Exports of display units rose in quantity and value. Statistics
show China exported 3.17 million display units during the
January-May period.
</P>
<P>
Printer exports stood at 2.07 million units.
</P>
<P>
China sold 379,000 matrix printers abroad during the first five
months, and it exported 860,000 laser printers. Meanwhile, it sold
800,000 inkjet printers abroad.
</P>
<P>
China's computer products have been entering the international
market with a sharpened competitive edge.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, imports and exports of computer products
reached an unprecedented high.
</P>
<P>
China sold 6.5 billion US dollars of computer products abroad
in 1996, up 30.4 percent from 1995. 
</P>
