<DOCNO> XIE19970706.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Becomes One of World's Big Gold Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is one of the world's
"big-ten" gold-producing countries with an annual production
capacity reaching 129 tons in 1996, Leo Hadi, country manager of
the World Gold Council (WGC) said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia was indeed a big gold producer but compared with the
world's need for gold which reached 3,000 tons a year, the
production level in the country was still low, Hadi said in
Denpasar, Bali on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said the biggest gold producer country in the world today
was Italy, but this country was also the biggest gold consumer
with an annual need for gold of 514 tons.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's gold industry had been developed for a long time
but its potential as an export commodity had not yet exploited
optimally, he said.
</P>
<P>
For the purpose, he said, the World Gold Council Indonesia was
holding a gold appreciation program which had been carried out
since 1993 through exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's main market for its gold export is the Middle East,
China (through Hong Kong) and the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
