<HEADLINE> Blast Kills 5 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil United Liberation
Front (TULF) MP, A. Thangathurai, was killed along with four
others in a bomb blast last night in Trincomalee town in Eastern
province, according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
When Thangathurai was to get into his vehicle after attending
an opening ceremony of a new building at Sri Shanmuga Vidyalayam,
a hand grenade was lobbed into the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
A. Thangathurai and four others, including the MP's bodyguard
and two school principals were killed and 15 people others injured
in the blast.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the assassination came amidst a top security
islandwide alert for possible Tamil rebel strike to mark "Black
July", the anniversary of the 1983 racial riots.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known who was responsible.
</P>
<P>
The police are conducting inquiries. However, no arrests have
been made yet so far.  
</P>
</TEXT>
