<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AIDS Sufferers in Indonesia May Reach 1 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Minister of Health
Sujudi has stated by year 2000 the AIDS sufferers in the country
may reach one million, unless urgent and early measures are taken.
</P>
<P>
The HIV/AIDS cases in the world, including Indonesia, continued
to increase along with a rise in sex-related diseases, and serious
measures must be taken, Sujudi said on Saturday in Semarang,
central Java, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
He said by year 2000, the number of HIV/aids affected people in
the world may reach 30 to 40 million, 80 percent of whom are in
Asia, including Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
At present, he said there are 560 people suffering from the
incurable disease. The actual total of the sufferers in Indonesia
should be higher, as many cases have not been reported to the
authorities, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the most effective way of staying away from HIV, which
causes AIDS, would be avoiding sexual intercourse other than with
one's wife or husband.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
