<HEADLINE> Rahilou Retains His WBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Khalid Rahilou succeeded in
defending his World Boxing Association light-welterweight title
Saturday by knocking American Marty Jakubowski in the seventh
round in Casablanca, Morocco.
</P>
<P>
It was the 30th victory of 31-year-old Rahilou's career.
</P>
<P>
Rahilou dominated the fight in the fourth round. Jakubowski
spent the next three rounds backing up before Rahilou finally got
him against the ropes with midway through the seventh round.
</P>
<P>
The American was put down twice in the round and was stopped
with 20 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
Rahilou took the WBA title last January against American
Frankie Randall in Nashville, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jakubowski, three years his junior, was ranked 8th by the WBA
and has been professional since the age of 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
