<HEADLINE> Sweden, Spain Advance to Top Four at Euro Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Sweden advanced to the
semi-finals of the European Women's Soccer Championships with a
3-0 victory over France in Karlskoga, Sweden on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Malin Andersson scored the first goal for the hosts with a
penalty at the 18th minute. Corimme Diacre scored an own goal
four minutes later, back-heeling the ball past goalkeeper Sandrine
Roux after a cross from the left flank. Kristin Jonsson completed
the scoring in the 45th.
</P>
<P>
In another match of Group A at Karlstad, one goal from Maria
Angele helped Spain to beat Russia 1-0 and advance to the final
four on goal difference over the French.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's victory finished it with a 3-0-0 record atop Group A,
while Spain and France both finished with 1-1-1 marks and four
points. But Spain scored two goals and allowed two in its three
matches while France was outscored 4-5.
</P>
<P>
The final Group B matches between defending world champion
Norway and Italy, and Denmark versus Germany, will be played in
the Norwegian cities of Lillestrom and Moss on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It's the first time in soccer history that two countries are
co-hosting a major tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
