<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 5 (Xinhua) -- World Champion Maria Brandin of
Sweden cruised into the final of the women's sculls at the Henley
Royal Regatta with an easy victory over Briton Bronwyn Roye in
Henley, England on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Brandin, who won the same race last year, moved comfortably
through her semifinal and will meet British international Guin
Batten in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish rower clocked a time of eight minutes and 21
seconds, while Batten won her race in a time four seconds slower.
</P>
<P>
British international Greg Searle faces compatriot and three
times world lightweight sculling champion Peter Haining, having
seen off a challenge by American Jamie Koven in the men's event.
</P>
</TEXT>
