<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy and Yugoslavia to Meet in European Basketball Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Yugoslavia will meet at
the final of the European Men's Basketball Championships after
respective victories over Russia and Greece in Barcelona on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Yugoslavia were always in control in their
88-80 win over Greece but the Italians were forced to come from
behind in their frantic 67-65 win over Russia.
</P>
<P>
Italy beat the Yugoslavs 74-69 in a group match earlier in the
competition, and are yet to lose a match in the tournament but
will nervetheless start the game as underdogs.
</P>
<P>
The Italians looked to be on their way out of the competition
after a poor start which left them 28-18 down.
</P>
<P>
Carlton Myers, tightly guarded by Russia's Sergei Babkov, was
slow to find his form.
</P>
<P>
But it was Myers who turned the game round, and with the
Russians giving up several vital possesions in the closing
minutes, the Italians were able to hang on.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Yugoslavia had played their best game of the
tournament to deal with the previously unbeaten Greek side.
</P>
<P>
Zeljko Obradovic's team went in at the break only four points
up, but quickly took control and surged to a 65-50 lead.
</P>
<P>
The Greeks closed to 74-68, and with five opponents in foul
trouble looked likely to give the reigning champions a close run.
</P>
<P>
But poor shot selection cost the Greeks the chance to draw
closer and the Yugoslavs kept their heads to run out comfortable
winners.
</P>
<P>
Two of Obradovic's key players are doubtful for Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
Aleksandar Djordjevic did not start the match and was troubled
by a leg injury throughout the game, particularly in the final
time-out.
</P>
<P>
The injury may limit Djordjevic's role in the final, while
fellow guard Predrag Danilovic pulled up at the end of the
semifinal with an ankle injury.
</P>
<P>
All four semifinalists have already guaranteed places in next
year's world championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
