<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Beats Cuba to Win World League Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Two-times men's volleyball world
champions Italy defeated Cuba in straight sets to win the eighth
World League finals here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by Michele Pasinato and Claudio Bonati, Italy
clinched their sixth league title with a 15-8, 15-5, 15-10 victory
in less than two hours to take the one million U.S. dollars first
prize.
</P>
<P>
It was Italy's second straight win against the Cubans in two
days. They defeated them three sets to one in a group match to
earn a place in the final.
</P>
<P>
Russia, urged on by some 8,000 home fans, earlier upset
reigning Olympic champions the Netherlands 15-8, 15-12, 15-8 in
the bronze medal match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
