<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boardman Wins Prologue of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- British rider Chris Boardman won the
prologue of the Tour de France in Rouen, France on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Boardman, who fell and crashed out of the 1995
Tour de France in the prologue stage, broke German Jan Ullrich's
hold on the lead as he came home in eight minutes 20.90 seconds,
two seconds better than last year's runner-up.
</P>
<P>
Russian Evgeni Berzin, the 1994 Tour of Italy winner, was third
in eight minutes 25.09 seconds. The 1996 Tour de France winner
Bjarne Riis finished 15 seconds off the pace, having been 7
seconds behind at the intermediate stage.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's first stage is the 192 kilometer run from Rouen to
Forges les Eaux. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
