<HEADLINE> Tour de France Cycling Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Following are the leading results of
the prologue stage of the Tour de France cycling race in Rouen,
France on Saturday, a 7.30km distance from Rouen to Rouen:
</P>
<P>
1. Chris Boardman, Britain, GAN, eight minutes 20 seconds
</P>
<P>
2. Jan Ullrich, Germany, TEL, 0:02
</P>
<P>
3. Evgeni Berzin, Russia, BAT, 0:05
</P>
<P>
4. Tony Rominger, Switzerland, COF, 0:05
</P>
<P>
5. Alex Zulle, Switzerland, ONC, 0:05
</P>
<P>
6. Peter Meinert, Denmark, USP, 0:07
</P>
<P>
7. Rolf Sorensen, Denmark, RAB, 0:10
</P>
<P>
8. Abraham Olano, Spain, BAN, 0:10
</P>
<P>
9. Laurent Brochard, France, FES, 0:11
</P>
<P>
10. Christophe Moreau, France, FES, 0:12
</P>
